    <h1>Gangtok and East Sikkim Itinerary - 3 Days, 2 Nights</h1>







    <h2>Day 1: Arrival in Gangtok</h2>



    <p>Upon arrival in Gangtok, check-in at your hotel and take some time to rest. In the afternoon, visit the following attractions:</p>



    <ul>



      <li><strong>MG Marg</strong> - Enjoy a leisurely walk and explore local shops and cafes.</li>



      <li><strong>Hanuman Tok</strong> - Visit the famous temple and enjoy panoramic views of the city.</li>



    </ul>



    <p>Return to your hotel for dinner and overnight stay.</p>







    <h2>Day 2: Excursion to Tsomgo Lake and Baba Mandir</h2>



    <p>After breakfast, proceed for a day trip to Tsomgo Lake and Baba Mandir. Enjoy the scenic drive and visit:</p>



    <ul>



      <li><strong>Tsomgo Lake</strong> - A glacial lake surrounded by snow-capped mountains.</li>



      <li><strong>Baba Mandir</strong> - A temple dedicated to Baba Harbhajan Singh, a revered soldier.</li>



    </ul>



    <p>Return to Gangtok in the evening for dinner and overnight stay.</p>







    <h2>Day 3: Departure via the Silk Route</h2>



    <p>After breakfast, check-out from the hotel and proceed towards East Sikkim through the Silk Route. On the way, visit:</p>



    <ul>



      <li><strong>Zuluk</strong> - A small village with stunning views of the Eastern Himalayas.</li>



      <li><strong>Thambi View Point</strong> - Enjoy breathtaking views of the Kanchenjunga range.</li>



    </ul>



    <p>Proceed to your onward journey.</p>







